# Documentation

## Canonical agent map

[docs/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md](../../docs/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md) — update when:

- Commands, CI, or Node version requirements change
- Architecture layers or sync flow change
- New risk areas or conventions are introduced

## Issue tracking & CI

- [docs/issue-tracking.md](../../docs/issue-tracking.md) — Project 4 Fluent Mobile Board, branch naming, PR linking (`Closes #NNN`)
- [docs/ci.md](../../docs/ci.md) — workflow inventory + future required-check guardrail

Update these when tracker policy or CI workflows change.

## Cursor rules

Keep `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` in sync with onboarding — short pointers only; avoid duplicating full onboarding content.

## README

[README.md](../../README.md) — human-focused setup (Android emulator, env vars). Link to `docs/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` for agents; do not duplicate full architecture there.

## QA preview testing

[docs/guides/qa-preview-testing.md](../../docs/guides/qa-preview-testing.md) — non-technical steps for PR previews (Fluent dev client, not Expo Go). Update when preview workflow comments or install flow change.

## PR template

[.cursor/templates/pr-template.md](../templates/pr-template.md) — update if required PR sections or verification steps change.

## Nested hot-path notes

Short pointers next to code (keep thin; link to full guides):

- [src/services/AGENTS.md](../../src/services/AGENTS.md)
- [src/db/AGENTS.md](../../src/db/AGENTS.md)

## Session env hook

Warn-only Cursor `sessionStart` hook: [`.cursor/hooks.json`](../hooks.json) + [`.cursor/hooks/session-env-check.sh`](../hooks/session-env-check.sh). Never deny tools.

## Style

- Short, scannable sections and tables
- Verify claims against code — do not invent behavior
- Prefer editing existing docs over new files
- No bloated architecture essays

## Do not

- Commit secrets, `.env`, or local-only files (e.g. `.bashrc`)
- Broad rewrites of README unless asked
- Create duplicate command lists without updating onboarding + `commands.mdc`
